         I KNOW that CHA has absolutely no effect on fear duration. How do I know this I hear you ask?</P><P>Simple I chose a nice quiet zone where nothing inherantly agros me, SK, and fear kited a Cyclops for over 2 hours using my wonderful invoke fear stick and my lowest level darkness just to slow the sucker down and make sure he came back to me.</P><P>During this excersise I kept the exact same gear on and repeated the fear 10 times before changing my CHA and repeating.</P><P>I varied my cha from 30, the lowest I can get it, to 147, the highest I can get it and almost everything in between. These was no discernable pattern that indicated that having a CHA of 30 was in any way better for fearing than having a CHA of 147.</P><P>Regardless of my CHA the duration of the fears was random sometimes lasting for 3 seconds sometimes lasting for 40 and all time frames between.</P><P>BTW this test also proves to me that the mobs MR has nothing at all to do with fear duration. MR **may** have something to do with the fear being resisted but if it sticks it is RANDOM. I say "may" becuase the victim of my tests resisted the invoke a number of times, about once in 20 casts, the resisted fears were not counted for averaging purposes.</P><P>Since doing that test at level 50 I have noticed that my fears seem to be lasting longer on average as I have gained levels, no hard evidence to back that up - just my gut feel.</P><P>I'm thinking about doing the same test using the Undead Cyclops as my Thralled pet. My intuition is that Thrall is the same way, with CHA having nothing at all to do with charm duration. This is from personal experience with a single long held charmed pet, once again the charm sometimes breaks before the Screaming Terror and sometimes lasts 5 or 6 minutes. Personally I have NEVER had a charmed pet last 8 minutes.</P><P>An interesting point about charm that I have noticed is that charm seldom seems to break when the charmed pet is moving from place to place. However this could be becuase the pet spends most of it's time standing still whacking on mobs.</P><P>Bottom line for me is that Ench Charm and Necro Charm are totally different. I personally think that necro CHA is a totally irrelevant statistic except for selling/buying to/from vendors.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
